StringWithMarkup.String: This classification aggregates experimental CCS data available in PubChem, from NORMAN-SLE, CCSbase, and Baker Lab.

Additional information can be found at the NORMAN-SLE (https://pubchem.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/classification/#hid=101), CCSbase (https://pubchem.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/classification/#hid=104), and Baker Lab (https://pubchem.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/classification/#hid=124) classifications.

nodes.description: The Unified Collision Cross Section (CCS) Compendium (drift tube MS) from Vanderbilt University, provided by Jackie Picache and John McLean. DOI:10.1039/C8SC04396E. Further details available here: https://lab.vanderbilt.edu/mclean-group/collision-cross-section-database/

nodes.description: A library containing the collision cross section (CCS) values of 311 adducts of 148 contaminants of emerging concern (CECs) and their metabolites measured with drift tube ion mobility high resolution mass spectrometry (in positive and negative ionization modes with N2 as drift gas) as described in Belova et al (2021) DOI:10.1021/acs.analchem.1c00142. Dataset DOI:10.5281/zenodo.4704648
This node contains CCS information from Baker Lab

DOI:10.1021/acs.est.2c00201 and Joseph et al. (2025) Scientific Data 12:150 DOI:10.1038/s41597-024-04363-0

Collision Cross Section (CCS) values from TOXCAST from the Baker and Rusyn Labs. The methods used to acquire these values are described in Teri et al (in prep.)

Collision Cross Section (CCS) values from antidepressants and metabolites from the Baker Lab.

nodes.description: This dataset is an entry point for users to contribute collision cross section values from the literature for addition to the NORMAN-SLE and the PubChem Collision Cross Section annotations.
